400:1 contrast ratio (typical)<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n| ext_display  = \n| rear_camera  = 12MP, \u0192/1.8 aperture, optical image stabilization, Six-element lens, True Tone flash, autofocus, 4K video recording at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps or 1080p HD video recording at 30 fps or 60 fps or 720p HD video recording at 30 fps, Cinematic video stabilization (4K, 1080p, and 720p), Slo\u2011mo video support for 1080p at 120 fps or 240 fps, Time\u2011lapse video with stabilization, Portrait mode, Portrait lighting, and Smart HDR\n| front_camera = \n| sound        = \n| connectivity = Wi-Fi 6 ([[802.11ax]])<br>[[4G]]\n| other        = [[IP Code|IP67]] IEC standard 60529 (splash, water, and dust resistant)\n| sar          = \n| hac          = \n| website      = {{URL|www.apple.com/iphone-se/}}\n| references   = \n}}\n{{iPhone models}}\nThe 2020 '''iPhone SE''' is a [[smartphone]] designed and marketed by [[Apple Inc.]] It is part of the 13th generation of the [[iPhone]], alongside the [[iPhone 11]], [[IPhone 11 Pro|iPhone 11 Pro and Pro Max]]. Announced on 15 April 2020 at 11 AM EST, the iPhone SE serves as a successor to both the [[iPhone SE (2016)|original iPhone SE]] and the [[iPhone 8]]. Pre-orders will begin on April 17, 2020, and it will be available on April 24, 2020.\n\n== History ==\nA successor to the [[iPhone SE]] has been rumoured since 2017, just a year after the device was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macrumors.com/2017/11/22/iphone-se-2-release-date-first-half-2018/|title=iPhone SE 2 Again Rumored to Launch in First Half of 2018|website=MacRumors|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\nThe phone also had two other rumoured names: ''iPhone SE 2'' and ''iPhone 9'', due to this phone sharing a design with the [[iPhone 8]].\n\nIn March 2020, cases for the phone were reportedly being shipped to [[Best Buy]],<ref name=\"9to5mac\">{{Cite web|url=https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|title=iPhone 9 case inventory arriving at Best Buy, other retailers with April 5 merchandising date|last=Miller|first=Chance|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403181051/https://9to5mac.com/2020/03/30/iphone-9-case-inventory-best-buy/|archive-date=April 3, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> showing an iPhone with an [[iPhone 8]]-sized body, a single camera lens for the regular model.<ref name=\"9to5mac\" /> [[Belkin]] screen protectors for the iPhone SE were also listed on the [[Apple Store|Apple web store]], cross-compatible with the regular-sized iPhone 8 and iPhone 7. However, the ''iPhone SE'' branding was quickly removed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-iphone-9-will-be-the-new-iphone-se|title=iPhone 9 will be called iPhone SE and could launch soon (Update)|website=Tom's Guide|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"9to5mac\" />\n\n== Design ==\nThe iPhone SE features a design with an aluminium frame, and its front and back are made out of glass. The phone's external design and dimensions are nearly identical to that of the iPhone 8, except for a centred Apple logo. It features bezels on the top and bottom of the front and a home button integrated with [[Touch ID]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|title=iPhone SE 2020: Everything We Know|website=MacRumors|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805112853/https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-se/|archive-date=August 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe iPhone SE is available in three colours; white, black,<!-- colours are not proper nouns --> and Product Red.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Colour name !!Front\n|-\n|White||Black\n|-\n|Black ||Black\n|-\n|Product Red <!-- Don't stylise per [[MOS:TM]] -->||Black\n|-\n|}\n\n== Specifications ==\n\n===Hardware===\nThe iPhone SE incorporates the [[Apple A13|Apple A13 Bionic]] system-on-chip (SoC) with an [[Apple A13|M13]] [[Apple motion coprocessors|motion coprocessor]]. It will be available in three internal storage configurations; 64 GB, 128 GB and 256 GB.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> The SE has a rating of IP67 under IEC standard 60529 for dust and water resistance.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> \n\n==== Display ====\nThe iPhone SE features the same Retina HD display found on the [[iPhone 8]]. However, [[Force Touch|3D Touch]] is replaced by Haptic Touch.\n\n==== Camera ====\nThe iPhone SE features a 12 MP rear camera similar to the wide camera of [[iPhone 11]] and [[iPhone 11 Pro]]. The camera has a \u0192/1.8 aperture, with autofocus, optical image stabilization, and a quad-LED True Tone flash. It is capable of recording 4K video at 24 fps, 30 fps, or 60 fps, 1080p HD video at 30 fps or 60 fps, or 720p HD video at 30 fps. The phone can also take panoramas up to 63 MP, and is capable of shooting photos in burst mode.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" />\n\nThe front camera of the iPhone SE is a 7 MP camera with \u0192/2.2 aperture and autofocus, capable of shooting 1080p HD video at 30 fps.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" />\n\nBoth the front and rear cameras of the iPhone SE support Smart HDR, Portrait mode and Portrait Lighting.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications\" /> Unlike the iPhone 11 and 11 Pro, iPhone SE does not support Night mode.\n\n===Software===\nThe iPhone SE will ship with [[iOS 13]] and supports Apple Pay<!-- Apple card is implicit with apple pay -->.<ref name=\"Official website: specifications />\n\n== Timeline of iPhone models ==\n{{Timeline of iPhone models}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{iOS}}\n{{Apple hardware since 1998}}\n{{Apple Inc. hardware}}\n{{Apple}}\n\n[[Category:IPhone|*]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2020]]\n[[Category:iOS]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2020]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications]]\n", "name_u